Here’s how ⬇️

Go out and get it. 

It’s that simple. 🤩 Life will give you a lot of reasons why not to— honestly our brains are trained that way from the time we’re tiny. Look for danger, i.e. what’s wrong with the situation/problem/relationship/job/business whatever. 

That’s cool. That part of your brain keeps you alive when a lion is chasing you. The problem is, there aren’t a lot of lions in my neighborhood. So then it turns into anxiety and stress and we get paralyzed with choices. 

Here’s the thing. Just take a step. Any step. Don’t worry if it’s right or wrong (those are constructs anyways) or if it will lead you the right place or not. Just take a step. 

Buy the course.
 Start the side hustle. 

Say the “I love you’s.”
 Take the trip. 

If you focus on the thing you want most - the why - then it will come to you. You may have to turn, or pivot or maybe not, but if you think about the end result you want more than the problems in front of you, you’ll manifest the relationship of your dreams. The time freedom you crave. Whatever that is to you, how you manifest it is you get very clear on what it is, then take baby steps and never lose sight. 

Next thing you know we’re on our way.

LOVE is a verb. An action word. 

It can be really easy, particularly this time of year, to get caught up in all the “stuff.” The to-do lists, the presents, the food, shopping lists, petty family members, all of it. 

I do my best when I get all the shopping done and out of the way early. Then I can just experience the love of the holidays. 

Things look different for me. This is the 4th year without my son. How we’ve survived this many I still don’t know. It’s like an open wound that never heals, but you learn to not rub salt scrub on it in the shower—you learn little tricks to minimize the sharp, stabbing pain. It never goes away, you always know it’s there, but you can do little things to make it more bearable that you figure out over time. 

If you have lost someone or are spending the holidays away from people you love, you know that this time of year can be really, really hard. Their absence is loud, heavy, and everywhere you turn. 

And yet, somehow around you life has gone on. People still smile. Families show up to the airport in matching Christmas jammies, or Go Navy gear, all to embrace someone off the plane. If it’s true, which it is, and what you focus on grows, then I invite you to focus on the love. On the verb of love. The actions people take.

Let that carry you through this next week. 

I see you - you are not alone and we can do this together. Happy Holidays to you. 

#grief #holidaysafterloss #love #loveisanactionword #loveisaverb #childloss #holidayseason

What even is Spiritual Marketing? ✨

To me it’s this idea of being aligned. Living your purpose. Aspiring to your higher self and calling in the clients, fans and customers that adore you 🥰

It’s the opposite of bro-marketing. It’s the antithesis of hustle culture 🚫

It is working hard, and tapping into the law of attraction, the law of reciprocity, and the karmic idea of putting good out into the world and attracting it back🍀.

You might say that’s not a marketing strategy. 

It’s a life strategy. 

It just happens to work for marketing too.
